-- New Zealand Ties 1-1 With Slovakia After Goal in Last Minute of Added Time
-- Bob Bensch
-- 2010-06-15T13:24:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-15/new-zealand-ties-1-1-with-slovakia-after-goal-in-last-minute-of-added-time.html

          
          
             New Zealand came from behind to tie
Slovakia 1-1 their soccer World Cup Group F match in Rustenburg,
South Africa.  
 Winston Reid scored in second-half injury time to give New
Zealand the tie. Robert Vittek scored in the 50th minute for
Slovakia.  
 Ivory Coast plays Portugal and 5-time champion Brazil faces
North Korea later today in Group G. Defending champion Italy
tied Paraguay 1-1 in the opening Group F game yesterday.  
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                            
                     
                     New Zealand's defender Winston Reid heads the ball to score a goal during their Group F first round 2010 World Cup football match. Photographer: Vincenzo Pinto/AFP/Getty Images  
                           

     
